choices.text:
the transport. There is just not enough of them. We have semi-decent taxi services, but taking them is expensive and it takes time to get anywhere. I am living within a kilometre of my friends and siblings, but braving the roads to cross the potholes and along slippery slopes is a big turn off. Time is a precious commodity, time-wasting can bring emotional agony and social stigma. The senior, need to look like she pays attention to every neighbours social status. Gaming her neighbours help looking after the neighbour, bus ride can make gossiping easily heard, messaging people can give signal that the person is on top of it. Playing a round is hours of fun and several made-up interesting story, not 10 seconds sms.

Living without transport is not so much a practical problem because everyone in Vanuatu understands getting along without, have to get things done somehow. The slightly-insane pastor ministering near bus shelters has a point when he says there other way of busing, he is talking about traditional way of moving herds of pigs. The pagautu, are smaller animals more manageable, that that would do for fast individual transfer. The beauty of pagautu is in individual control.
